50|$|In early 1943, the Topf & Söhne fitter Heinrich Messing {{installed}} exhaust {{fans in the}} Auschwitz II crematoria {{and also}} in <b>the</b> <b>gas</b> <b>chambers.</b> Initially, <b>the</b> process of <b>gassing</b> prisoners and then letting fresh air into <b>the</b> <b>gas</b> <b>chambers</b> lasted several hours, but after the exhaust fans were installed this was reduced to about an hour, thus reducing the turn around time.|$|R
